and integrity  If their commitment is not complete  their stay at the Institute may be short  Conduct Above all else  cadets are expected to conduct themselves as men and women of character at all times  Exemplary conduct both at and away from the Institute reflects credit on the cadet  the Corps  and the Institute  Civility Cadets are expected commit to respectful living  treating everyone with dignity and fairness  Cadets come to understand the impact of their behavior on others and strive to exemplify civility  Trust Cadets live and learn in an environment of trust  Their daily lives and conduct are regulated by the traditions and rules of the Institute and a very simple code of honor  Cadets trust one another because their word is their bond   Our world needs women and men of principle who will stand for values and beliefs despite the costs  despite any ridicule or scorn  Matt Waalkes  13 Valedictorian More about Matt Viewbook Links College Fairs FAQs Financial Aid Tuition   Fees Schedule VMI s Institutional Profile Follow  Then lead  Resources VMI CEEB Code  005858 Financial Aid FAFSA Code  003753 Students and their families are encouraged to use a variety of information sources to select a college and major  The State Council of Higher Education for Virginia  SCHEV  provides one such source that is available here  Contact Us VMI Office of Admissions 319 Letcher Avenue Lexington  VA 24450 P  540 464 7211 P  800 767 4207 F  540 464 7746 admissions vmi edu Don t do ordinary  EXPERIENCE VISIT APPLY COSTS   AID CONTACT Our honor code is one of our most treasured traditions  Stan Okoye  13  Vice President Honor Court More about Stan Our honor code is one of our most treasured traditions  Stan Okoye  13  Vice President Honor Court More about Stan Our honor code is one of our most treasured traditions  Stan Okoye  13  Vice President Honor Court More about Stan Our honor code is one of our most treasured traditions  Stan Okoye  13  Vice President Honor Court More about